  "prompt": "Are there any scholarships in MBBS program in Germany for Pakistani students?",
  "response": "While Germany offers some scholarship opportunities for international students, the situation for MBBS/medical scholarships specifically for Pakistani students is limited. Here are some potential options:\n\n1. DAAD Scholarships\n- Offers some scholarships for international students\n- Competitive selection process\n- Covers tuition and living expenses partially\n\n2. Heinrich B\u00f6ll Foundation Scholarships\n- Available for postgraduate students\n- Supports students with good academic records\n- Requires German language proficiency\n\n3. Erasmus Mundus Scholarships\n- European Union funded program\n- Covers some medical and health-related programs\n- Competitive selection\n\n4. Government-specific scholarships\n- Pakistani government scholarships\n- bilateral exchange programs\n\nImportant considerations:\n- Most German medical programs are taught in German\n- Requires high German language proficiency (B2/C1 level)\n- Medical education in Germany is different from Pakistani system\n- Typically requires passing a qualifying exam\n\nRecommended steps:\n- Check individual university websites\n- Contact German embassy in Pakistan\n- Explore DAAD scholarship portal\n- Verify specific eligibility criteria\n\nWhile opportunities exist, they are limited and highly competitive. Students should prepare comprehensive applications and demonstrate strong academic credentials.",
